			<abstract label="Abstract:">Audio tapes and files relating to research on rent control
				and progressive urban politics in Santa Monica, California.</abstract>
			<langmaterial label="Language:">Collection material in <language encodinganalog="041" langcode="eng">English</language></langmaterial>
		</did>
		<scopecontent encodinganalog="MARC 520">
			<head id="a3">COLLECTION DESCRIPTION</head>
			<p>Audio tapes and files relating to research on rent control and progressive urban
				politics in Santa Monica, Ca. include handwritten notes from interview tapes,
				transcripts of earlier interviews conducted by Dale Eunson, a file about the
				Campaign for Economic Democracy (CED), selected letters to the editor, documents
				from the opponents to Santa Monicans for Renters' Rights (SMRR), miscellaneous
				background information about the rise of SMRR, a file on organizational issues, and
				a file with various election materials. Audio tapes are of interview conducted with
				SMRR participants, city officials, senior tenants' rights activists, younger
				activists, landlords and other opponents of SMRR and rent control, and some public
				hearings.</p>
		</scopecontent>
